  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Somalia El Nino Drought Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ADRA proposes to implement a 2-month emergency assistant to drought-affected victims in Puntland, and intervention that will provide relief by addressing severe water shortage for the affected families. The project targets 2,500 people (418 households) in the pastoral communities in the Puntland state of Somalia through emergency water trucking at a rate of 45 liters per day/household.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Some parts of Northern Somalia have been experiencing severe drought since 2015. Authorities in Somaliland and Puntland have both declared the drought a disaster and issued appeals for assistant to an estimated 385,000 people in both states. ADRA has implemented a number of projects in Puntland, including the affected villages within Sool and Nugal regions. Currently, ADRA Somalia is implementing an EU-funded education project under a consortium of four NGOs. However, this current project does not have a component through which help can be extended to the affected population.</narrative>
  </description>
